    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small books adapted so as to be conveniently carried in a person's pocket. Use of the term to denote a printed book does not seem to have been common before the 20th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>方便置於口袋隨身攜帶的特製小型書本；以此詞彙指稱印刷書籍的用法似乎要到二十世紀以後才比較普遍。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleines Buch, das von einer Person bequem in der Tasche getragen werden kann. Diese Bezeichnung für ein gedrucktes Buch scheint vor dem 20. Jahrhundert nicht gebräuchlich gewesen zu sein.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
